claim.claim-text:
1. A thermal retention hood for reducing heat loss from a patient's head during surgery and recovery, comprising:
a flexible enclosure configured to enclose the face and head of the patient and retain heat within the enclosure;
a first perforated line in the enclosure in a position corresponding to the patient's nose and mouth;
a second perforated line defining a removable panel of the enclosure corresponding to the location of the patient's face, the removable panel adapted for removal to uncover only the patient's face while leaving the remainder of the enclosure on the patient's head to provide retention of heat within the remainder of the enclosure; and
a strap configured to secure an open end of the enclosure around the patient's neck.
